n be returned to any library on campus except for course reserve materials journals and theses which must be returned directly to the swain library fines for reserve items are $1.00 per hour applied in full at 16 minutes after the time due stiff fines are also levied for recalled items that are not returned promptly especially items recalled for course reserves two weeks after a due date a bill to replace the item as well as a non refundable fee of $5 per item is assessed recalls books and dissertations are subject to recall if requested by another user all recalled items must be returned within 7 days of the date on the notice you receive the recall overdue fine accrues at the rate of $3.00 per day recalled items may not be renewed chemistry and chemical engineering toxicology and chemical safety group menu back stanford university stanford california 94305 650 725 1064 terms of use copyright complaints
